               <provenance>The original donor(s) or commissioners may be
                     those indicated in the prologue of the Vita (4rb):
                     Śahlä Rufāʾel, followed by a name which was erased with the exception of the
                     last letter (b); his mother Walatta Qāl and his father Tasfā Mikāʾel. It seems
                     that in many cases the second word in the rubricated name Śahlä Rufāʾel was
                     later deleted and Śǝllāse was added instead (usually in black ink), to make
                     Śahlä Śǝllāse out of it. In the same way, the name Walatta Qāl was transformed
                     into Walatta Takla Hāymānot. 
 Śahlä Śǝllāse, Walatta Śǝllāse, Walatta
                     Takla Hāymānot, Walda Sǝmʿon are mentioned in the supplication formulas on
                        29va, 36ra, 43ra, 54rb, 73ra, 93vb, 99va,
                     106rb, 109ra, 110va and passim. In most of the cases the names are added in a
                     different, somewhat later hand. On 129rb, an
                     addition to the supplication formula indicates that Walatta Śǝllāse acquired
                     the book with her own means.</provenance></history>
